_AC_ANIME_DURATION.description: (?) Sets the length of the next animation.

_MACRO_TALKMSG.description: Shows a textbox with the given message.

_MACRO_TALK_KEYWAIT.description: Shows a textbox with the given message.

_MACRO_EASY_OBJ_MSG.description: Combines the commands _TALK_OBJ_START, _TALKMSG, _TALK_CLOSE, and _TALK_OBJ_END to show a textbox.

_NOP.description: Unused. Ends the script. Functionally the same as _END.

_TIME_WAIT.description: Waits for the amount of frames provided, then continues execution.

_CMPWK.description: Compares the value of a variable to the value of another variable. Used once in unused poison scripts.

_IF_JUMP.description: Used after _CMPWK. Used once in unused poison scripts.

_IFVAL_JUMP.description: Compares two values, then jumps to a script if true.

_IFVAL_CALL.description: Compares two values, then calls a script if true.

_IFWK_JUMP.description: Compares the value of a variable to a value, then jumps to a script if true.

_SWITCH.description: Begins a switch statement based on the value of a variable.

_CASE_JUMP.description: Compares the value of the variable given to the last _SWITCH command ran to another value, then jumps to a script if they are equal.

_CASE_CANCEL.description: Compares the value of the variable given to the last _SWITCH command ran to the value of "Cancel", then jumps to a script if they are equal.

_IF_FLAGON_JUMP.description: Checks a flag and if it is set, jumps to a script.

_IF_FLAGOFF_JUMP.description: Checks a flag and if it isn't set, jumps to a script.

_IF_FLAGON_CALL.description: Checks a flag and if it is set, calls a script.

_IF_FLAGOFF_CALL.description: Checks a flag and if it isn't set, calls a script.

_FLAG_SET_WK.description: Sets the flag designated by the value of a variable.

_TRAINER_FLAG_CHECK.description: Checks a trainer flag. Used in conjunction with _IF_TR_FLAGON_JUMP, _IF_TR_FLAGON_CALL, _IF_TR_FLAGOFF_JUMP, or _IF_TR_FLAGOFF_CALL.

_IF_TR_FLAGON_JUMP.description: Checks a trainer flag. If it is set, jumps to a script.

_IF_TR_FLAGOFF_JUMP.description: Unused. Checks a trainer flag. If it isn't set, jumps to a script.

_IF_TR_FLAGON_CALL.description: Unused. Checks a trainer flag. If it is set, calls a script.

_IF_TR_FLAGOFF_CALL.description: Unused. Checks a trainer flag. If it isn't set, calls a script.

_ADD_WK.description: Add to the value of a variable.

_SUB_WK.description: Subtract to the value of a variable.

_LDVAL.description: Set a variable to a value.

_LDWK.description: Set a variable to a value.

_TALKMSG_ALLPUT.description: Only used in unused Pal Park scripts.

_TALKMSG_NG_POKE_NAME.description: Presumably is supposed to show a textbox with all Battle Tower illegal Pokémon.

_TALKMSG.description: Shows a textbox with the given message.

_TALKMSG_SP.description: (?) Only used in union room. Presumably shows a textbox.

_TALKMSG_AUTOGET.description: Only used in one common script, unused otherwise.

_AB_KEYWAIT.description: (?) Some sort of key wait usually used before doing a screen fade-out.

_AB_KEY_TIME_WAIT.description: (?) Some sort of key wait with a timer. Only used in union room.

_TALK_CLOSE_NO_CLEAR.description: Closes the currently open textbox. Used before shop commands. Functionally the same as _TALK_CLOSE.

_TALK_KEYWAIT.description: Shows a textbox with the given message. Functionally the same as _TALKMSG.

_EASY_OBJ_MSG.description: Combines the commands _TALK_OBJ_START, _TALKMSG, _TALK_CLOSE, and _TALK_OBJ_END to show a textbox.

_BOARD_REQ_WAIT.description: (?) Waits on a board request made previously with command _BOARD_REQ.

_BOARD_END_WAIT.description: (?) Waits until the board is closed, then puts a value in a variable. Functionally the same as _BOARD_MSG.

_EASY_INFOBOARD_MSG.description: Shows an info sign message. Mostly used for Gym signs.

_MENU_REQ.description: (?) Menu request. Presumably opens the menu?

_YES_NO_WIN.description: Opens a Yes/No choice window, then puts the result in a variable.

_BMPMENU_MAKE_LIST.description: (?) Adds an option to the unused choice menu previously initialized by _BMPMENU_INIT or _BMPMENU_INIT_EX.

_BMPMENU_START.description: (?) Shows the unused choice menu previously initialized by _BMPMENU_INIT or _BMPMENU_INIT_EX.

_BMPLIST_MAKE_LIST.description: (?) Adds an option to the unused choice menu previously initialized by _BMPLIST_INIT.

_BMPLIST_START.description: (?) Shows the unused choice menu previously initialized by _BMPLIST_INIT.

_SE_STOP.description: Stops a specific sound effect that is playing.

_SE_WAIT.description: Waits for a playing sound effect to finish before continuing.

_VOICE_WAIT.description: Waits for a playing Pokémon cry to finish before continuing.

_EASY_VOICE_MSG.description: Combines multiple commands to show a textbox and play a Pokémon cry.

_ME_PLAY.description: Plays a fanfare. Functionally the same as _SE_PLAY.

_ME_WAIT.description: Waits for a playing fanfare to finish.

_SND_INITIAL_VOL_SET.description: (?) Sets the volume of a sound effect. Only used once in the player's room during the intro.

_BGM_PLAY.description: Overrides the background music completely until _BGM_NOW_MAP_PLAY is called.

_BGM_STOP.description: Unused. Presumably stops the currently playing background music.

_BGM_NOW_MAP_PLAY.description: Plays the background music associated with the current map.

_BGM_SPECIAL_SET.description: Unknown use. Only used 4 times in the game.

_BGM_FADEOUT.description: Fades the background music out to the specified volume.

_BGM_FADEIN.description: Only used once in an unused script.

_PLAYER_FIELD_DEMO_BGM_PLAY.description: Plays the specified background music. Used for Dawn/Lucas, Rival, and getting shown around.

_CTRL_BGM_FLAG_RESET.description: Unknown use. Only used once during the Spear Pillar cutscenes.

_PERAP_DATA_CHECK.description: Unused. Checks if there is Chatot cry data and put the result in a variable.

_PERAP_REC_START.description: Unused. Start recording the Chatot cry.

_PERAP_REC_STOP.description: Unused. Stop recording the Chatot cry.

_PERAP_SAVE.description: Unused. Save the recorded Chatot cry.

_SND_CLIMAX_DATA_LOAD.description: (?) Loads extra sound data during the Spear Pillar cutscenes.

_OBJ_ANIME.description: Animates an actor based on a given animation script.

_ANIME_DATA.description: (?) Executes an animation command without needing a separate script.

_OBJ_ANIME_WAIT.description: Waits for the current actor animations to finish before resuming execution.

_OBJ_PAUSE_ALL.description: Pauses the movement of all actors.

_OBJ_PAUSE_CLEAR_ALL.description: Unpauses the movement of all actors.

_OBJ_PAUSE.description: Pauses the movement of an actor.

_OBJ_PAUSE_CLEAR.description: Unpauses the movement of an actor.

_VANISH_DUMMY_OBJ_DEL.description: Unknown use. Only used once during the first Lake Verity visit.

_TURN_HERO_SITE.description: Turns the actor to face the player.

_TALK_OBJ_START.description: Starts an object event with the actor turning to face the player. Combination of _TALK_START, _TALK_OPEN, and _TURN_HERO_SITE.

_TALK_OBJ_START_TURN_NOT.description: Starts an object event with the actor only turning their head to face the player. Combination of _TALK_START, _TALK_OPEN, and some third command.

_TALK_OBJ_END.description: Ends an object event. Combination of _TALK_CLOSE and _TALK_END.

_PLAYER_POS_GET.description: Gets the player's current XZ position and puts it into two variables.

_OBJ_POS_GET.description: Unused. Presumably gets the position of the actor the player is interacting with.

_PLAYER_POS_OFFSET_SET.description: (?) Sets the player's position to specific coordinates. Only used in Battle Tower.

_PLAYER_DIR_GET.description: Gets the direction the player is facing.

_NOT_ZONE_DEL_SET.description: Unknown use. Used in relation to partner trainers (Barry, Cheryl, etc.).

_MOVE_CODE_CHANGE.description: (?) Changes the movement associated with an actor.

_PAIR_OBJID_SET.description: Sets an actor as the partner trainer following the player.

_EVENT_DATA.description: Unknown use. Only used in the Oreburgh Gym.

_EVENT_DATA_END.description: Unknown use. Only used once in Oreburgh Gym.

_SCENE_CHANGE_LABEL.description: Jumps to a script which contains map script commands.

_SCENE_CHANGE_DATA.description: Calls a script of the main script file if the value of a variable matches a specific value.

_SCENE_CHANGE_END.description: Ends the script containing the map script commands.

_FLAG_CHANGE_LABEL.description: Calls a script of the main script file.

_OBJ_CHANGE_LABEL.description: Calls a script of the main script file.

_COMP_GOLD.description: Checks if the player has an amount of money.

_GOLD_WIN_WRITE.description: Shows a window with the player's money.

_COIN_WIN_WRITE.description: Shows a window with the player's coins.

_COIN_WIN_DEL.description: Removes the window showing the player's coins.

_COIN_WRITE.description: Updates the amount shown in the window showing the player's coins.

_ADD_ITEM.description: Gives an amount of one item to the player.

_SUB_ITEM.description: Takes an amount of an item from the player.

_ADD_ITEM_CHK.description: Gives an amount of one item to the player after checking if they have enough bag space.

_ITEM_CHK.description: Checks if the player has an amount of an item.

_WAZA_ITEM_CHK.description: Checks if an item is a TM/HM.

_GET_POCKET_NO.description: Gets which pocket an item goes in.

_CHECK_POCKET.description: Checks if any item is present in a given pocket.

_ADD_GOODS.description: Gives an amount of one good to the player. Only used in one unused common script.

_ADD_TRAP.description: Gives an amount of one trap to the player. Only used in one unused common script.

_ADD_TAMA.description: Gives an amount of one sphere to the player.

_CB_ITEM_NUM_GET.description: Checks how many of a seal the player has.

_CB_ITEM_NUM_ADD.description: Gives an amount of one seal to the player.

_UNKNOWN_FORM_GET.description: Gets the form of an Unown.

_ADD_POKEMON.description: Gives a Pokémon to the player.

_ADD_TAMAGO.description: Gives an egg to the player.

_CHK_POKE_WAZA.description: Checks if a Pokémon in a specific position has a specific move.

_APPROVE_POISON_DEAD.description: Unknown use. Only used once in unused poison scripts.

_REVENGE_TRAINER_SEARCH.description: Checks if a trainer is currently looking for a rematch.

_SET_MAP_PROC.description: Refreshes the map after commands that load a new scene.

_FINISH_MAP_PROC.description: Finishes refreshing the map after closing the town map in a Pokémon Center.

_WIFI_AUTO_REG.description: Registers a friend in the Pal Pad (DP). Likely does nothing.

_COMM_GET_CURRENT_ID.description: Checks if this player is the host of the Battle Tower multi-battle group or if they joined.

_DENDOU_NUM_GET.description: Gets the amount of times the player has entered the Hall of Fame.

_POKE_WINDOW_PUT.description: Opens a window showing a Pokémon.

_POKE_WINDOW_PUT_PP.description: Opens a window showing a Pokémon. Only used in Chatot scripts.

_POKE_WINDOW_DEL.description: Closes a window showing a Pokémon.

_POKE_WINDOW_ANM.description: Animates the Pokémon shown in a window.

_POKE_WINDOW_ANM_WAIT.description: Waits for the animation of the Pokémon shown in a window to end.

_BTL_SEARCHER_EVENT_CALL.description: Checks the battery of the VS Seeker.

_BTL_SEARCHER_DIR_MV_SET.description: Unknown use. Something related to the VS Seeker.

_IMAGE_CLIP_VIEW_CON_SET_PROC.description: Unknown use. Something related to contests.

_TMAP_BG_SET_PROC.description: Opens the Town Map from Pokémon Centers.

_OEKAKI_BOARD_SET_PROC.description: (?) Shows a menu related to the Union Room.

_TR_CARD_SET_PROC.description: Opens the trainer card of another player in Union Room.

_TRADE_LIST_SET_PROC.description: Opens the trade menu in Union Room.

_RECORD_CORNER_SET_PROC.description: Opens the Record Corner menu in Union Room.

_DENDOU_SET_PROC.description: Adds an entry to Hall of Fame.

_PC_DENDOU_SET_PROC.description: Opens the Hall of Fame records menu.

_FIRST_POKE_SELECT_SET_AND_DEL.description: Sets the selected starter to some place in memory. Used right after _FIRST_POKE_SELECT_PROC.

_BAG_SET_PROC_KINOMI.description: Opens the bag menu in Berry mode.

_BAG_GET_RESULT.description: Puts the chosen item in the bag into a variable.

_UNION_POKELIST_SET_PROC.description: (?) Opens the party in Union Room.

_POKELIST_GET_RESULT.description: Returns the chosen Pokémon in the previous Pokémon selection menu.

_EYE_TRAINER_MOVE_SET.description: Moves the trainer(s) that just saw the player.

_EYE_TRAINER_MOVE_CHECK.description: Checks if the trainer that was just moved by _EYE_TRAINER_MOVE_SET is still moving.

_EYE_TRAINER_TYPE_GET.description: Gets the type of fight that was started. (Single, double, two trainers)

_EYE_TRAINER_ID_GET.description: Gets the ID of the trainer(s) that saw the player.

_WIPE_FADE_START.description: Unknown use. Only used in unused scripts.

_WIPE_FADE_END_CHECK.description: Waits for a fade-in or fade-out to end.

_WHITE_IN.description: Fades the screen back in from white.

_BLACK_IN.description: Fades the screen back in from black.

_MAP_CHANGE.description: Warps the player to a map.

_MAP_CHANGE_NONE_FADE.description: Warps the player to a map without fading.

_ITEM_NAME.description: Puts the name of the given item into a buffer.

_TEMOTI_MONSNO.description: Gets the NatDex Number of the Pokémon in slot #<Slot> of the player's party and returns it in <Result>.

_AC_UP.description: Moves the affected actor up an amount of tiles over an amount of frames.

_AC_DOWN.description: Moves the affected actor down an amount of tiles over an amount of frames.

_AC_LEFT.description: Moves the affected actor left an amount of tiles over an amount of frames.

_AC_RIGHT.description: Moves the affected actor right an amount of tiles over an amount of frames.

_AC_DIR_U.description: Turns the affected actor up over an amount of frames.

_AC_DIR_R.description: Turns the affected actor right over an amount of frames.

_AC_DIR_D.description: Turns the affected actor down over an amount of frames.

_AC_DIR_L.description: Turns the affected actor left over an amount of frames.

_AC_DIR_VAL.description: Turns the affected actor to a specific angle over an amount of frames.

_AC_WAIT.description: Waits for the specified amount of frames before continuing the movement script.

_AC_MARK_GYOE.description: Shows a [!] bubble above the affected actor.

_AC_HERO_MATCH_X.description: Moves the affected actor up or down to match the X position of the player.

_AC_HERO_MATCH_Z.description: Moves the affected actor left or right to match the Z position of the player.

_AC_UP_CENTER.description: Moves the affected actor up an amount of tiles over an amount of frames. The actor ends on the center of the final tile.

_AC_DOWN_CENTER.description: Moves the affected actor down an amount of tiles over an amount of frames. The actor ends on the center of the final tile.

_AC_LEFT_CENTER.description: Moves the affected actor left an amount of tiles over an amount of frames. The actor ends on the center of the final tile.

_AC_RIGHT_CENTER.description: Moves the affected actor right an amount of tiles over an amount of frames. The actor ends on the center of the final tile.

_AC_DIR_UP_CENTER.description: (?) Turns the affected actor up and centers it on the tile.

_AC_DIR_LEFT_CENTER.description: (?) Turns the affected actor left and centers it on the tile.

_AC_DIR_RIGHT_CENTER.description: (?) Turns the affected actor right and centers it on the tile.

_AC_DIR_PAUSE_ON.description: Locks the direction of the affected actor.

_AC_DIR_PAUSE_OFF.description: Unlocks the direction of the affected actor.

_TURN_HERO_TALK_OBJ.description: Turns the player to face the actor.

_FADE_SPEED.description: Sets the speed of fade-ins and fade-outs.

_AC_INDEX_ANIME.description: Animates the affected actor with a specific animation.

_AC_INDEX_ANIME_WAIT.description: Waits for the currently playing animation from AC_INDEX_ANIME to end.

_AC_MARK_EMO.description: Shows an emotion bubble above the affected actor.

_AC_NECK_ROTATE.description: Rotates the head of the affected actor.

_IMAGE_CLIP_VIEW_CON_CHECK_PROC.description: Unknown use. Something related to contests.

_AC_FACE_INDEX.description: Changes the face of the affected actor.

_TALK_OBJ_START_LOOK_NONE.description: Starts an object event without the actor turning to face the player. Combination of _TALK_START and _TALK_OPEN.
